data.meta_description: May 30, 2024 - Mary Tudor, favourite sister of King Henry VIII, was feted around Europe for her pale skin and good looks. Henry arranged for Maryâ€™s marriage to the aging and gouty King Louis XII as part of a peace treaty with France, however he died suddenly; Mary was Queen of France for just 82 days. Unafraid to challenge Henry, she then persuaded the king that her next marriage should be for love...
